@page "/gamerules/headtails"
@using GoplayasiaBlazor.Core.Global.Interface;
@using GoPlayAsiaWebApp.Goplay.Games.Shared;
@attribute [Authorize(Roles = "1")]
@inject ICurrentUser icurrentUser
<section class="pt-2">
    <main class="container pt-4">
        <h5 class="font-weight-bold mt-2 text-light">HEADS OR TAILS HOUSE RULES</h5>
        <div class="">
            <div class="container bg-white text-dark pb-2 pt-4">
                <h4 class="mt-5 mb-2">I. Minimum/MaximumBet Limit and Payout Odds</h4>
                <table class="w-100 text-center">
                    <tr>
                        <td class="font-weight-bold">Details</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Min bet</td>
                        <td>P100</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Max bet</td>
                        <td>P10,000</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Payout Odds</td>
                        <td>1=195%</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Combination</td>
                        <td>HHT - HEADS</td>
                        <td>HHH - HEADS</td>
                        <td>TTH - TAILS</td>
                        <td>TTT - TAILS</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>

                <h4 class="pt-2">GAME RULES</h4>

                <ol>
                    <li>Player bets on Head or Tails;</li>
                    <li>Three (3) coins shall be inserted shall be into a coin lot to roll down through an acrylic guide and into an enclosed acrylic bin;</li>
                    <li>Simultaneous Drop – 3 coins are dropped at the same time in the bin.</li>
                    <li>Results will be based on the majority (Heads or Tails) on whatever side is shown after it lands. (i.e. HHT = H; HHH = H or TTH = T; TTT = T);</li>
                    <li>Minimum bet P100; Maximum bet P10,000;</li>
                    <li>
                        The game is cancelled or considered void when the following conditions are met:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Overlapping of coin/s – Whether partially or completely;</li>
                            <li>Coin/s that lands vertically; and</li>
                            <li>Coin/s bouncing out of the gaming bin;</li>
                            <li>Once these conditions are met, all bets are returned and will proceed to the next game.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>In case of discrepancy or malfunction in the conduct of the game, all bets and games shall be voided.</li>
                    <li>1=195%</li>
                </ol>
                <h4 class="">Dealing Procedures</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>The Dealer shall look at the Dealer's Dashboard (with attached camera) before and after the deal for instruction or guidance.</li>
                    <li>Accepting of bets through remote gaming platform ensue when the status on the Dealer Dashboard reads "OPEN".</li>
                    <li>Player bet/s for desired combination/s Head or Tales. Once the player clicks his/her choice/s, the bet amount option pop-up, either enter preset chip denominations or manually key-in amount then click "PLACE BET," otherwise "CANCEL".</li>
                    <li>A confirmation button shall appear for the player to confirm selected bet option and amount by clicking "Yes", otherwise "No".</li>
                    <li>The system timer starts until the allotted period for betting ends. System automatically disables all access for betting and changes the status to "CLOSED".</li>
                    <li>
                        At the conclusion of betting, the Dealer shall start with the dealing procedure in the following sequence:
                        <ul>
                            <li>The Dealer shall retrieve the coins from the square acrylic box.</li>
                            <li>Upon retrieval, the Dealer shall drop the 3 coins through the coin slot.</li>
                            <li>The Dealer then shall declare encode the winning outcome in the Dealer's Tablet for the Game Validator's confirmation.</li>
                            <li>After Dealer determines the game result, another validation of result shall be made by the Proponent remotely and on a separate module ("Validator"). Only after confirmation of the result, the winning bet/s shall be processed.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Dealer shall perform this dealing cycle continuously during his stint until he is relieved by another Dealer, the last deal has been announced, or the table needs to undergo maintenance.</li>
                    <li>The game is void if any coin/s overlapped, bounced out of the gaming bin and/or has not landed flat on the gaming bin.  All bets are returned and the dealer will proceed to deal the next game.</li>
                    <li>In case of system failure, malfunction, and/or error, the Gaming Operator has the right to declare any and all of the affected game/s and winning/s as invalid and void, and to recover from the account of the affected player any payments made as a result of said system failure, malfunction and/or errors without the need of consent from the said player. This clause shall not be considered to be excluding liability for anything which it would be unlawful to exclude under applicable law.</li>
                    <li>Bets can’t be cancelled once confirmed but can be increased within the duration of betting time.</li>
                    <li>Philippine Peso Currency is converted into Token with a 1:1 ratio or value.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center pb-5 mt-3">
                <a href="/games/headstails" class="btn gpa-btn">Back to the Game</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
</section>
